# Frontend design (auto when editing UI files)

When changing visuals in matched files, read `.cursor/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md` and follow it.

Quick rules:
- Plan palette/type/layout in 5–10 lines before editing CSS.
- Keep existing `--primary` green family; extend, don't replace with unrelated themes.
- Prioritize scannable hierarchy for low-literacy users (size + color for key vs sub text).
- Do not change simulation, survey, or Supabase logic unless the user explicitly asks.
